{"audit_id": "audit_a362f3f9975d56c29d282f3c", "problem_id": "prob_20e7806428521f0a8aafd57e", "record_type": "problem_main_record", "field_name": "normalized_question_text", "before_value": "As shown in the figure, $AD$ is the median of $ \\triangle ABC$, $CE$ is the median of $ \\triangle ACD$. If the area of $ \\triangle ABC$ is $12\\text{cm}^2$, what is the area of $ \\triangle CDE$?", "after_value": "As shown in the figure, $AD$ is the median of $ \\triangle ABC$, $CE$ is the median of $ \\triangle ACD$. If the area of $ \\triangle ABC$ is $12\\text{cm}^2$, what is the area of $ \\triangle CDE$?", "change_type": "text_normalized", "trigger": "NormalizationAgent", "operator_type": "system", "created_at": "2026-04-03T17:52:49Z"}
{"audit_id": "audit_40e48cdd6f5d4f0af34406e5", "problem_id": "prob_20e7806428521f0a8aafd57e", "record_type": "problem_main_record", "field_name": "normalized_answer_text", "before_value": "\\textbf{Solution:} Since $AD$ is the median of side $BC$ of $\\triangle ABC$, and the area of $\\triangle ABD$ is $12\\text{cm}^2$,\\\\\ntherefore, the area of $\\triangle ADC$ is: $\\frac{1}{2}\\times 12=6\\text{cm}^2$,\\\\\nSince $CE$ is the median of side $AD$ of $\\triangle ACD$,\\\\\ntherefore, the area of $\\triangle CDE$ is: $\\frac{1}{2}\\times 6=\\boxed{3}\\text{cm}^2$.", "after_value": "\\textbf{Solution:} Since $AD$ is the median of side $BC$ of $\\triangle ABC$, and the area of $\\triangle ABD$ is $12\\text{cm}^2$,\\\\\ntherefore, the area of $\\triangle ADC$ is: $\\frac{1}{2}\\times 12=6\\text{cm}^2$,\\\\\nSince $CE$ is the median of side $AD$ of $\\triangle ACD$,\\\\\ntherefore, the area of $\\triangle CDE$ is: $\\frac{1}{2}\\times 6=\\boxed{3}\\text{cm}^2$", "change_type": "answer_canonicalized", "trigger": "NormalizationAgent", "operator_type": "system", "created_at": "2026-04-03T17:52:49Z"}
